I made this tonight and it was as delicious as previous reviewers stated! Using 1.68 lb. sirloin: for marinade, quadrupled the (lite) soy sauce and sugar and doubled the salt. In sauce, doubled the soy sauce, kept the sesame oil and the cornstarch the same as listed, doubled the sherry and sugar, and used about 3/4 cup of beef broth (made with bouillon cube). For the remaining ingredients, used two large cloves of garlic and about 2 T. of fresh ginger, 1 1/2 t. of red pepper flakes and the oil called for. I included asparagus pieces, red peppers, sliced mushrooms and carrots. I would recommend that these other vegetables be cut into fairly large pieces. My husband and I thought it was as good as any Beef with Vegetable dish we've had in one of the better Chinese restaurants!

