Rating: 3
This was a great dish and my boyfriend continues to rave about it. For the marinade, I used Kikkoman soy sauce and so, did not add any salt to the marinade. I also did not add any cooking wine (didn't have it on hand) and it still tasted great. I added extra veggies to the stir fry, including 1/2 brown onion (sliced), and half of a green and red bell pepper (leftovers from another dish). You can really add any veggies that you like. Don't let the broccoli steam for too long because it will end up too soft by the time you add the beef. And for the final touch, I gave the dish 2-3 splashes of oyster sauce to add the little bit of salt that was needed. Don't forget the red pepper flakes! They add a nice kick to the dish- you'll also get a nice aroma if you let saute the garlic/onions/ginger on high heat and let them burn a little. I will definitely make this dish again-simple, flavorful, not bland like most beef and broccoli dishes.

